  <h2>What Andover Sellers Typically Look Like</h2>
  <p>Most Andover sellers aren't in distress — they're in transition. Relocating executives, upsizing or downsizing families, investors who bought in Andover when it was cheaper and are now cashing out. The property values are higher, which means the gap between a cash offer and retail listing is larger too.</p>
  <p>That said, Andover has its share of older homes in the original part of town that need significant work. Homes built in the 70s and 80s near the older neighborhoods can have deferred maintenance issues that make a traditional sale complicated. We see those regularly.</p>
